cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of removing text overlays and inpainting the occluded parts in videos without any input masks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning-based framework, which involves the use of encoder-decoder models and recurrent feedback, indicating that it could fall under the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which could place it under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves the use of temporal aggregation, which could place it under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
